Dear Ralf,

thanks for putting this online.  However, one general thing:  please avoid
usage of 

> \begin{verbatim}

long text

> \end{verbatim}

since this causes the long text to be saved and downloaded as an image, which
is a nuisance if your internet connection is not that good.

Bill, is there a way to make escaping better?  Best thing would be, in my
opinion, to process pages entirely written in LaTeX with tex4ht.  structured
text is nice for short stuff, but LaTeX is really much better for anything
which is a bit more involved.

Many thanks,

Martin




